# Copy this file to .env.local and fill values before running the frontend
# Replace the placeholders with values from your Auth0 Application (Single Page App)

VITE_AUTH0_DOMAIN=YOUR_AUTH0_DOMAIN.auth0.com
VITE_AUTH0_CLIENT_ID=YOUR_AUTH0_CLIENT_ID
# Optional: If you use an API/audience in Auth0 you can set it here
# VITE_AUTH0_AUDIENCE=YOUR_AUTH0_API_AUDIENCE
# Backend API URL (production). Example: https://applyperfect-backend.onrender.com
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend.example.com

# Notes:
# - After creating an Auth0 Application (Single Page Application) add these URLs to the Allowed Callback URLs / Logout URLs / Web Origins:
#   http://localhost:5173
#   http://localhost:5174
#   http://localhost:5175
#   http://localhost:3000
#   (and your production origin when deployed)
# - To enable Google sign-in in Auth0, open the Auth0 Dashboard -> Authentication -> Social -> Google, and configure the Google connection.
#   You can either use Auth0's preconfigured provider or supply your own Google OAuth client ID & secret.
# - Ensure the Google social connection is toggled ON for your Application under Applications -> [Your App] -> Connections.
# - Keep secrets out of source control. Use a real `.env.local` (not checked in) with the real values.
